Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: oldest-supported-numpy
Version: 0.2
Summary: Meta-package that provides the oldest supported version of Numpy
Home-page: https://reproject.readthedocs.io
Author: Thomas Robitaille
Author-email: thomas.robitaille@gmail.com
License: BSD
Platform: UNKNOWN
Requires-Python: >=3.5
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.13.3) ; python_version == "3.5" and platform_system != "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.16.0) ; python_version == "3.5" and platform_system == "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.13.3) ; python_version == "3.6" and platform_system != "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.16.0) ; python_version == "3.6" and platform_system == "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.14.5) ; python_version == "3.7" and platform_system != "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.16.0) ; python_version == "3.7" and platform_system == "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.17.3) ; python_version >= "3.8" and platform_system != "AIX"
Requires-Dist: numpy (==1.17.3) ; python_version >= "3.8" and platform_system == "AIX"

This is a meta-package which can be used in ``pyproject.toml`` files to
automatically provide the oldest supported version of Numpy without having to
list them all. In other words::

    [build-system]
    requires = [
        "wheel",
        "setuptools",
        "numpy==1.13.3; python_version=='3.5',
        "numpy==1.13.3; python_version=='3.6',
        "numpy==1.14.5; python_version=='3.7',
        "numpy==1.17.3; python_version>='3.8'
    ]

can be replaced by::

    [build-system]
    requires = ["wheel", "setuptools", "oldest-supported-numpy"]

And as new Python versions are released, the ``pyproject.toml`` file does not
need to be updated.


